summary:
An education in Architectural Engineering and Project Management and practical experience as an Energy Consultant and Project Engineer has led me to where I am today: bringing innovative and sustainable solutions to life. 

I am a sustainable design, smart city, and circular economy enthusiast. I aspire to push the 'reusable movement' into common practice by implementing a circular, reusable packaging service with the innovative start-up, Zero Impack. Let's make singe-use packaging obsolete!

I followed an undergraduate education in Architectural Engineering and a Master's in Construction Engineering Management. I am now a professional equipped with a fine balance of engineering skills and a business mindset. My professional personality can be summarized as follows:

-- Innovation and sustainability drives me every day;

-- I'm committed to my team and look to inspire;

-- Face mistakes: learning and growing is a never-ending journey;

-- I'm devoted to delivering quality to my team and my clients; 

-- I design, build, and innovate for the future.

I enjoy making new professional acquaintances. Reach out if you want to talk reusable packaging, quantum mechanics, green buildings, or basketball.
